article.headline: Central Connecticut 73, New Hampshire 66
article.story: kwho DURHAM, N.H. (AP) -- Central Connecticut guards Javier Mojica and Tristan Blackwood combined for 55 points as the Blue Devils defeated the University of New Hampshire Wildcats 73-66 on Saturday. Mojica led the scoring charge with 15 points to give Central Connecticut (1-3) a 37-34 advantage at the half, then scored another 16 points in the second. The Blue Devils led by as much as 17 with 12:48 remaining. But UNH (0-3) cut the gap to four points with 1:48 left as the Wildcats' Jermaine Anderson posted 14 second-half points. Mojica all but ended any hopes of a comeback for the Wildcats after he converted a foul shot to put the Blue Devils up 69-64. He missed his second attempt, but raced to the middle and grabbed the offensive rebound, forcing UNH to foul. Central Connecticut's Chris Winters then sank two free throws with 11 seconds remaining to secure the win. Blackwood scored 24 points.
